25
00:01:54.420 --> 00:02:00.433
Splunk is a data analysis platform and
Splunk Enterprise provides SIEM solutions.

26
00:02:00.433 --> 00:02:06.776
Splunk Enterprise is a self-hosted tool
used to retain, analyze, and search an

27
00:02:06.776 --> 00:02:13.225
organization's log data to provide security
information and alerts in real-time.

28
00:02:13.225 --> 00:02:20.467
Splunk Cloud is a cloud-hosted tool used
to collect, search, and monitor log data.

29
00:02:20.467 --> 00:02:26.428
Splunk Cloud is helpful for organizations
running hybrid or cloud-only environments,

30
00:02:26.428 --> 00:02:31.031
where some or all of the organization's
services are in the cloud.

31
00:02:32.031 --> 00:02:34.064
Finally, there's Google's Chronicle.

32
00:02:34.064 --> 00:02:40.816
Chronicle is a cloud-native tool designed
to retain, analyze, and search data.

33
00:02:40.816 --> 00:02:46.386
Chronicle provides log monitoring,
data analysis, and data collection.

34
00:02:46.386 --> 00:02:48.229
Like cloud-hosted tools,

35
00:02:48.229 --> 00:02:53.524
cloud-native tools are also fully
maintained and managed by the vendor.

36
00:02:53.524 --> 00:02:58.410
But cloud-native tools
are specifically designed to take full

37
00:02:58.410 --> 00:03:03.567
advantage of cloud computing
capabilities such as availability,

38
00:03:03.567 --> 00:03:06.201
